  "prompt": "Is yahoo near half as successful as Google?",
  "response": "Yahoo and Google operate in the same online search and advertising space, but their business models and levels of success differ significantly. Google, founded in 1998, has grown to dominate the search engine market and online advertising, becoming one of the most valuable companies in the world with a market capitalization often exceeding $1 trillion.\n\nYahoo, on the other hand, was one of the early internet pioneers but struggled to maintain its relevance in the face of fierce competition from Google and others. While Yahoo still has a substantial user base and offers various services (like email, news, and finance), its market share in search is much smaller compared to Google. Yahoo was sold to Verizon in 2017 and later merged with AOL to form Oath (now known as Verizon Media), which highlights its decline in the tech industry.\n\nIn summary, while Yahoo remains a well-known brand, it does not come close to Google in terms of market share, revenue, or overall success. Thus, it would be an exaggeration to say that Yahoo is \"half as successful\" as Google; the disparity is much larger.",
